# Orchestrator Integration — Walkthrough

## Summary

All **245 tests passed** across the entire HelioX RAG 3.0 test suite, including the end-to-end [test.pdf](file:///c:/HelioX/test.pdf) integration test that exercises the full orchestration pipeline.

## Bugs Fixed in Orchestrator

Six contract mismatches were found and resolved between [orchestrator.py](file:///c:/HelioX/tests/test_orchestrator.py) and its downstream services:

| # | Bug | Fix |
|---|-----|-----|
| 1 | `QueryAnalyzer.analyze()` is async, returns [QueryAnalysisResponse](file:///c:/HelioX/query_pipeline/schemas.py#142-149) wrapper | Added `await`, extract `.sqo` from response |
| 2 | `CrossChunkSynthesizer.synthesize()` arg order is [(outputs, sqo)](file:///c:/HelioX/run_test_pdf.py#13-46) | Swapped arguments in orchestrator call |
| 3 | [synthesize()](file:///c:/HelioX/synthesis/synthesizer.py#31-117) returns [SynthesisResult](file:///c:/HelioX/synthesis/schemas.py#98-109), not a tuple | Changed to `synthesis_result = ...` and access `.merged_claims` / `.conflict_candidates` |
| 4 | [AdjudicationEngine](file:///c:/HelioX/adjudication/engine.py#30-278) method is [adjudicate()](file:///c:/HelioX/adjudication/engine.py#39-123), not `resolve_conflicts()` | Changed method name, pass [(synthesis_result, outputs)](file:///c:/HelioX/run_test_pdf.py#13-46) |
| 5 | [AdjudicationResult](file:///c:/HelioX/adjudication/schemas.py#89-101) has `updated_confidence`, not `global_agreement_score` | Fixed field reference in confidence gate |
| 6 | Redis mock was `MagicMock`, not async-compatible | Replaced with `AsyncMock` for session memory |

